  "prompt": "How do I solve cubic ecuations if I am only allowed to use windows calculator and a piece of paper?",
  "response": "To solve cubic equations using only a Windows calculator and paper, you can use the following method:\n\n1. First, write down the standard form of the cubic equation: \n   ax\u00b3 + bx\u00b2 + cx + d = 0\n\n2. Use the cubic formula (Cardano's formula) or try these steps:\n   - Try to guess one rational root first\n   - Use synthetic division to find other roots\n   - Use the calculator for calculations\n\nGuessing a rational root:\n- List factors of the constant term (d)\n- Try these as potential roots by dividing the entire equation\n- If (x - r) divides evenly, r is a root\n\nSynthetic Division:\n- If you find a root r, divide the cubic by (x - r)\n- This reduces the cubic to a quadratic\n- Solve the quadratic using the quadratic formula\n- Use calculator for calculations\n\nExample:\nx\u00b3 - 6x\u00b2 + 11x - 6 = 0\nPotential roots: \u00b11, \u00b12, \u00b13, \u00b16\nTry 1: (x - 1) divides evenly\nReduce to quadratic and solve remaining roots\n\nWould you like me to walk you through a specific cubic equation?",
